// BUG-041: wolf_http_res_status missing forward declaration + wolf_req_strdup OOM gap
// Class: P1 — Runtime Stability (silent NULL propagation into arena)
// Trigger: OOM condition during wolf_req_strdup (or calling wolf_http_res_status before
//          its definition after adding the OOM guard to wolf_req_alloc)
// Expected: HTTP 503 returned cleanly; no corrupt output; no implicit-function-declaration warning
// Actual (before fix):
//   1. clang -Wimplicit-function-declaration warning on wolf_http_res_status at line ~877
//   2. wolf_req_strdup NULL strdup result silently registered with arena → 
//      subsequent code dereferences NULL → SIGSEGV or corrupt response
// Fixed: Added wolf_http_res_status forward declaration at line 159.
//        Added NULL/OOM guard to wolf_req_strdup matching wolf_req_alloc pattern.

func main() {
    // Minimum script that exercises wolf_req_strdup at HTTP request time.
    // To trigger the OOM path manually: inject ulimit -v or fault malloc in test harness.
    $s = "hello"
    print($s)
}
